[0629/141628.804:INFO:CONSOLE(8)] "Extension->Webview(PassthroughRequest-reply): {"data":{"data":[{"id":1,"name":"brainstorming","latestVersion":"1","description":"You MUST use this before any creative work - creating features, building components, adding functionality, or modifying behavior. Explores user intent, requirements and design before implementation.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":674,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 10:15:08"},{"id":10,"name":"writing-plans","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use when you have a spec or requirements for a multi-step task, before touching code","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":618,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 10:15:12"},{"id":5,"name":"requesting-code-review","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use when completing tasks, implementing major features, or before merging to verify work meets requirements","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":526,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:17"},{"id":9,"name":"web-design-guidelines","latestVersion":"1","description":"Review UI code for Web Interface Guidelines compliance. Use when asked to \"review my UI\", \"check accessibility\", \"audit design\", \"review UX\", or \"check my site against best practices\".","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":502,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"vercel-labs/agent-skills","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 12:03:24"},{"id":6,"name":"test-driven-development","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use when implementing any feature or bugfix, before writing implementation code","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":394,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-28 13:52:23"},{"id":4,"name":"obsidian-markdown","latestVersion":"1","description":"Create and edit Obsidian Flavored Markdown with wikilinks, embeds, callouts, properties, and other Obsidian-specific syntax. Use when working with .md files in Obsidian, or when the user mentions wikilinks, callouts, frontmatter, tags, embeds, or Obsidian notes.","iconUrl":"http://autowork-saas-online.bj.bcebos.com/v1/skills/obsidian-markdown/1/assets/icon_20260413203736_SVgypp.png?authorization=bce-auth-v1%2FALTAK4WXisf7r9g6u22qW40P30%2F2026-04-13T12%3A37%3A36Z%2F-1%2F%2F14e61be313988ad795c2ab0587c8f21af84e0b9a830cffc9c38820ac16c86f68","downloadCount":372,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"kepano/obsidian-skills","updatedAt":"2026-06-28 16:52:35"},{"id":7,"name":"using-git-worktrees","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use when starting feature work that needs isolation from current workspace or before executing implementation plans - creates isolated git worktrees with smart directory selection and safety verification","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":356,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:19"},{"id":3,"name":"finishing-a-development-branch","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use when implementation is complete, all tests pass, and you need to decide how to integrate the work - guides completion of development work by presenting structured options for merge, PR, or cleanup","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":344,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"superpowers","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:21"},{"id":2,"name":"copywriting","latestVersion":"1","description":"When the user wants to write, rewrite, or improve marketing copy for any page — including homepage, landing pages, pricing pages, feature pages, about pages, or product pages. Also use when the user says \"write copy for,\" \"improve this copy,\" \"rewrite this page,\" \"marketing copy,\" \"headline help,\" \"CTA copy,\" \"value proposition,\" \"tagline,\" \"subheadline,\" \"hero section copy,\" \"above the fold,\" \"this copy is weak,\" \"make this more compelling,\" or \"help me describe my product.\" Use this whenever someone is working on website text that needs to persuade or convert. For email copy, see email-sequence. For popup copy, see popup-cro. For editing existing copy, see copy-editing.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":329,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"coreyhaines31/marketingskills","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:22"},{"id":8,"name":"vercel-react-best-practices","latestVersion":"1","description":"React and Next.js performance optimization guidelines from Vercel Engineering. This skill should be used when writing, reviewing, or refactoring React/Next.js code to ensure optimal performance patterns. Triggers on tasks involving React components, Next.js pages, data fetching, bundle optimization, or performance improvements.","iconUrl":"http://autowork-saas-online.bj.bcebos.com/v1/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/1/assets/icon_20260413203738_SPZMkr.png?authorization=bce-auth-v1%2FALTAK4WXisf7r9g6u22qW40P30%2F2026-04-13T12%3A37%3A38Z%2F-1%2F%2F78498561ddaef0aa9ce7d51595f6a4c589f8eecf725f9530afa9a33d546d287a","downloadCount":315,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"vercel-labs/agent-skills","updatedAt":"2026-06-28 16:53:45"},{"id":18,"name":"frontend-dev","latestVersion":"1","description":"Full-stack frontend development combining premium UI design, cinematic animations,\nAI-generated media assets, persuasive copywriting, and visual art. Builds complete,\nvisually striking web pages with real media, advanced motion, and compelling copy.\nUse when: building landing pages, marketing sites, product pages, dashboards,\ngenerating media assets (image/video/audio/music), writing conversion copy,\ncreating generative art, or implementing cinematic scroll animations.\n","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":22,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:25"},{"id":14,"name":"content-factory","latestVersion":"1","description":"Multi-agent content production system. One piece of source content becomes many formats — social posts, email, scripts, headlines, and more. Five specialized agent personas: Writer, Remixer, Editor, Scriptwriter, and Headline Machine.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":11,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:28"},{"id":25,"name":"markitdown-skill","latestVersion":"1","description":"Convert documents to Markdown using the `markitdown` CLI. Supports PDF, Word, PowerPoint, Excel, images (OCR), audio (transcription), HTML, YouTube, and URLs. Use when a user wants to convert a file or URL to Markdown, extract text from PDFs/images, transcribe audio/video, or batch-convert documents.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":11,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:26"},{"id":21,"name":"github","latestVersion":"1","description":"Interact with GitHub using the `gh` CLI. Use `gh issue`, `gh pr`, `gh run`, and `gh api` for issues, PRs, CI runs, and advanced queries.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":10,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:29"},{"id":35,"name":"web-scraper","latestVersion":"1","description":"Web scraping and content comprehension agent — multi-strategy extraction with cascade fallback, news detection, boilerplate removal, structured metadata, and LLM entity extraction","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":10,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:31"},{"id":17,"name":"excalidraw-diagram","latestVersion":"1","description":"Create Excalidraw diagrams for workflows, architectures, protocols, concepts, and system explanations. Use when a user wants a flowchart, architecture sketch, visual explanation, or diagram as a .excalidraw file plus PNG preview. Includes a local Playwright renderer for visual QA and reference files for palette, JSON structure, and reusable element patterns.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":9,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:32"},{"id":22,"name":"impeccable","latestVersion":"1","description":"Create distinctive, production-grade frontend interfaces with high design quality.\nUse this skill when the user asks to build web components, pages, artifacts, posters, or applications\n(examples include websites, landing pages, dashboards, React components, HTML/CSS layouts, or when\nstyling/beautifying any web UI). Generates creative, polished code and UI design that avoids generic\nAI aesthetics.\n\nTrigger scenarios — use when the user mentions any of:\n- UI design, frontend design, web design, interface design, 界面设计, 前端设计\n- responsive layout, mobile adaptation, breakpoints, 响应式, 自适应, 适配\n- animation, motion, micro-interaction, transitions, 动画, 动效, 微交互\n- UX copy, microcopy, error messages, labels, UX 文案, 文案优化\n- performance optimization, bundle size, rendering, 性能优化, 渲染, 加载速度\n- accessibility audit, a11y, WCAG, 无障碍, 可访问性\n- design review, design critique, UX evaluation, 设计评审, 设计审查\n- typography, fonts, type hierarchy, 字体, 排版, 字号\n- color palette, color scheme, theming, 配色, 色彩, 主题\n- layout, spacing, visual rhythm, grid, 布局, 间距, 视觉节奏\n- simplify UI, declutter, reduce noise, 精简, 简化, 去噪\n- design system, components, tokens, 设计系统, 组件库, token\n- edge cases, error handling, i18n, overflow, 边缘情况, 容错, 国际化\n- onboarding, empty state, first-run experience, 引导, 空状态, 新手体验\n- visual impact, make it bold, more personality, 视觉冲击, 更大胆, 更有个性\n- tone down, calmer, less aggressive, 降噪, 更柔和, 更克制\n- polish, finishing touches, pre-launch QA, 打磨, 最终检查\n- extraordinary effects, shaders, scroll-driven, 炫酷效果, 非凡视觉\n- normalize, consistency, design drift, 规范化, 一致性\n- extract components, refactor patterns, 提取组件, 复用模式\n","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":9,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:58"},{"id":11,"name":"agent-team-orchestration","latestVersion":"1","description":"Orchestrate multi-agent teams with defined roles, task lifecycles, handoff protocols, and review workflows. Use when: (1) Setting up a team of 2+ agents with different specializations, (2) Defining task routing and lifecycle (inbox → spec → build → review → done), (3) Creating handoff protocols between agents, (4) Establishing review and quality gates, (5) Managing async communication and artifact sharing between agents.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:57"},{"id":12,"name":"awesome-design-md","latestVersion":"1","description":"Curated collection of 54 reusable DESIGN.md files for developer-focused interfaces. Use when a user wants to build UI that matches a specific brand's design system, needs a DESIGN.md template, asks for design tokens/color palettes/typography of known products, or says 'make it look like [brand]'. Load the matching reference file and use it as the design spec.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:56"},{"id":13,"name":"canvas-design","latestVersion":"1","description":"Create beautiful visual art in .png and .pdf documents using design philosophy. You should use this skill when the user asks to create a poster, piece of art, design, or other static piece. Create original visual designs, never copying existing artists' work to avoid copyright violations.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-28 18:48:52"},{"id":16,"name":"darwin-skill","latestVersion":"1","description":"Darwin Skill (达尔文.skill): autonomous skill optimizer using an evaluate-improve-validate loop. Evaluates SKILL.md files using an 8-dimension rubric (structure + effectiveness), runs hill-climbing with git version control, validates improvements through test prompts, and generates visual result cards. Use when user mentions \"优化skill\", \"skill评分\", \"自动优化\", \"auto optimize\", \"skill质量检查\", \"达尔文\", \"darwin\", \"帮我改改skill\", \"skill怎么样\", \"提升skill质量\", \"skill review\", \"skill打分\".","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:54"},{"id":19,"name":"github-ai-trends","latestVersion":"1","description":"Generate GitHub AI trending project reports as formatted text leaderboards. Fetches top-starred AI/ML/LLM repos by daily, weekly, or monthly period and renders a styled leaderboard. Use when the user asks for AI project trends, GitHub trending, AI leaderboard, or wants to see popular AI repos.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:53"},{"id":24,"name":"llm-wiki","latestVersion":"1","description":"Build and maintain a personal knowledge base (wiki) using LLMs. Instead of RAG-style retrieval, the LLM incrementally compiles, cross-references, and maintains a persistent structured wiki from raw sources. Use when user wants to create a knowledge base, build a personal wiki, organize research notes, ingest documents into a structured wiki, or maintain a living knowledge repository.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:52"},{"id":28,"name":"minimax-pdf","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use this skill when visual quality and design identity matter for a PDF. CREATE (generate from scratch): \"make a PDF\", \"generate a report\", \"write a proposal\", \"create a resume\", \"beautiful PDF\", \"professional document\", \"cover page\", \"polished PDF\", \"client-ready document\". FILL (complete form fields): \"fill in the form\", \"fill out this PDF\", \"complete the form fields\", \"write values into PDF\", \"what fields does this PDF have\". REFORMAT (apply design to an existing doc): \"reformat this document\", \"apply our style\", \"convert this Markdown/text to PDF\", \"make this doc look good\", \"re-style this PDF\". This skill uses a token-based design system: color, typography, and spacing are derived from the document type and flow through every page. The output is print-ready. Prefer this skill when appearance matters, not just when any PDF output is needed.\n","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:50"},{"id":33,"name":"skill-vetter","latestVersion":"1","description":"Security-first skill vetting for AI agents. Use before installing any skill from third-party or unknown sources. Checks for red flags, permission scope, and suspicious patterns.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":8,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:49"},{"id":23,"name":"infographic-maker","latestVersion":"1","description":"Generate hand-drawn cartoon-style infographics from articles, concepts, reports, or data. Use when a user wants a visual summary, knowledge card, illustrated overview, or one-page explainer. Distill 3-7 key points, map them to concrete visual metaphors, and produce a single 16:9 infographic image with minimal text and strong visual hierarchy.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":7,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:48"},{"id":27,"name":"mcporter","latestVersion":"1","description":"Use the mcporter CLI to list, configure, auth, and call MCP servers/tools directly (HTTP or stdio), including ad-hoc servers, config edits, and CLI/type generation.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":7,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:46"},{"id":29,"name":"obsidian","latestVersion":"1","description":"Work with Obsidian vaults (plain Markdown notes) and automate via obsidian-cli.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":7,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:44"},{"id":30,"name":"pdfkit-py","latestVersion":"1","description":"Pure-Python PDF toolkit with 50 commands covering reading, editing, conversion, forms, encryption, OCR, and IR. Trigger on: PDF 阅读, 编辑, 转换, 合并, 拆分, 加密, 签名, OCR, 表单, 水印, 书签, 压缩, 裁剪, 旋转, pdfkit.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":7,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:43"},{"id":34,"name":"tutor-skills","latestVersion":"1","description":"Turn PDFs, docs, and codebases into Obsidian StudyVaults with structured notes, then quiz yourself with concept-level progress tracking. Use when users want to study documents, create study materials from files, generate practice questions, or track learning mastery.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":7,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:40"},{"id":15,"name":"content-ops","latestVersion":"1","description":"Score, evaluate, and iteratively improve any content or strategy using an auto-assembled panel of domain experts. Handles copy, sequences, landing pages, strategy docs, titles, charts, recruiting evaluations, or anything else that needs a quality gate. Recursively iterates until all scores hit 90+ (max 3 rounds). Use when asked to: \"expert panel this\", \"score this\", \"rate these variants\", \"quality check this\", \"panel review\", \"which version is better\", \"expert score\", \"evaluate this copy/strategy/page\", or when another skill needs a quality gate on its output. Also triggers on: \"score this landing page\", \"expert panel these email variants\", \"rate this headline\", \"panel these charts\".","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":6,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:42"},{"id":20,"name":"github-trending-cn","latestVersion":"1","description":"GitHub Trending Monitor. Fetch GitHub trending repos by daily/weekly/monthly period using real GitHub Search API. Runs scripts/github_trending.py (no pip deps, stdlib only). Use when user asks for 今日热门, 本周热门, 本月热门, GitHub trending, 开源动态, or popular repos. Supports language filter (python/javascript/go/rust etc.) and GITHUB_TOKEN for higher rate limits. 触发词：GitHub、trending、开源、热门项目.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":6,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:37"},{"id":26,"name":"mcp-builder","latestVersion":"1","description":"Guide for creating high-quality MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers that enable LLMs to interact with external services through well-designed tools. Use when building MCP servers to integrate external APIs or services, whether in Python (FastMCP) or Node/TypeScript (MCP SDK).","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":6,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-28 16:52:58"},{"id":31,"name":"remotion-video-toolkit","latestVersion":"1","description":"Complete toolkit for programmatic video creation with Remotion + React. Covers animations, timing, rendering (CLI/Node.js/Lambda/Cloud Run), captions, 3D, charts, text effects, transitions, and media handling. Use when writing Remotion code, building video generation pipelines, or creating data-driven video templates.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":6,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:39"},{"id":32,"name":"shader-dev","latestVersion":"1","description":"Comprehensive GLSL shader techniques for creating stunning visual effects — ray marching, SDF modeling, fluid simulation, particle systems, procedural generation, lighting, post-processing, and more.","iconUrl":null,"downloadCount":6,"createBy":"d6a689d5-cd0b-4595-b385-8aeb1b058710","source":"comate","updatedAt":"2026-06-29 11:12:36"}],"code":200,"message":null,"status":null},"status":200,"headers":